column4: Lil Dicky is the voice of the voiceless.   His debut mixtape So Hard has been categorized as “funny” and “impressive” by his friends. His first commercial album Professional Rapper debuted at #7 on the Billboard Hot 200 and #1 on both the comedy and rap charts.    A non-traditional rapper Lil Dicky uses a mix of comedy lyrical ingenuity and self-deprecation to spew out entertaining and relatable content.   When he was 14 he opened up for the R&B group 112 at his overnight camp. He’s been rapping ever since.   Currently he’s had sex with nineteen women but he’s hoping that number goes up with time patience and a positive outlook.   At night he’ll pee sitting down due to fatigue.   Join him on his quest to change rap forever.
